<subsubsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-a-trapezium">
    <title>Area of a Trapezium</title>
    <p>
       
    </p>
    <p>
       A trapezium is a four-sided polygon (quadrilateral) that has one pair of opposite sides that are parallel.
        These parallel sides are called the bases of the trapezium. 
       The other two sides are not parallel and are called the legs.
    </p>
    <p>
        Proterties of a trapezium.
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul marker="square">
            <li>
                <p>
                     A trapezium looks like a bridge. Suggest other three real life examples of trapeziums.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    One pair of sides are parallel (they never meet).
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The height is the straight-up distance between the parallel sides.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The angles inside add up to 360°.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <image width="50%">
    <latex-image label="Trapezium-one">
