    <p>
        The area of a trapezium is given by the formula:
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow>\text{A} =\amp \frac{\text{a+b}}{2}\text{h}  </mrow>
        </md>
        where a and b are the two parallel sides and h height.
    </p>
